news.title: Amid Evergrande crisis, more Chinese developers to issue asset-backed securities
news.para: Country Garden, the country's top property developer, said on Sunday that the company is considering applying for the issuance of supply chain asset-based securities (ABS) in the near term.

news.title: In four months, 290 acres of government land recovered in Bengaluru
news.para: Of the 290 acres recovered from July 31 to November 27 this year, 237 are in lake/tank beds. The lake encroachments were cleared at 155 places, with Anekal taluk reporting the highest recovery.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance to raise Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: ​​The base issue size of the bonds, in the nature of secured redeemable non-convertible debentures (NCDs), is of Rs 200 crore with an option to retain over subscription up to Rs 800 crore, aggregating up to Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: Centre to implement 105 smart city projects in Puducherry at Rs 822 crore
news.para: The ministry has issued work orders for 42 projects costing 163.89 crore while tenders have been issued for nine projects which cost 40.47 crore. Detailed project reports have been prepared for 51 projects at a cost of 604.68 crore.

news.title: Experion Developers to invest $350 million to fuel India expansion
news.para: Experion is developing townships, group-housing projects, commercial landmarks, organised retail destinations, hotels and resorts across Andhra Pradesh, Delhi NCR, Goa, Haryana, Maharashtra, Punjab, Tamil Nadu and Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Nagpur improvement trust forces society to demarcate plots for third time
news.para: On January 1, TOI reported how 317 plots owners are running pillar to post for constructing houses on their plots for the last five years following construction of an overhead water tank and road by the NIT on some plots instead of the public utility (PU) land.

news.title: HC raps Bengaluru development body for not taking over park, CA site in layout
news.para: A division bench of chief justice Ritu Raj Awasthi and justice Sachin Shankar Magadum gave this direction while disposing of a PIL filed by M Venkatesh, a resident of Bengaluru.

news.title: CIDCO gets blanket NOC from AAI on buildings height near Navi Mumbai airport
news.para: Therefore, the applicants seeking development permissions and occupancy certificates had to approach individually the AAI for getting the No Objection Certificates, the City and Industrial Development Corporation (CIDCO) said in a release.

news.title: China's Guangdong summons Evergrande's chairman after debt repayment warning
news.para: On Friday, Evergrande said in a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange it had received a demand from creditors to pay about $260 million. It is already late paying $82.5 million in coupons due on Nov. 6.

news.title: Ludhiana: Panel approves installation of UID number plate with QR code
news.para: According to GIS survey conducted by the MC officials, there are more than 4 lakh properties in 37 blocks. The GIS survey was conducted with the help of Punjab Remote Sensing Centre (PRSC).

news.title: Income tax department searches on realty group in Surat
news.para: The search at the leading realty group at a time when the sector in the state is reeling under slowdown for the past several months sent shockwaves among realtors.

news.title: India Accelerator to add 2.5 lakh sq ft of flexible space by FY22-23
news.para: With investment pipeline of one million USD, the company plans to reach 300,000 sq ft of operational area by FY 22-23.

news.title: Bengaluru: Need for space propels demand for layouts in suburbs
news.para: Healthy living and physical distancing are triggering a trend in plotted property purchases in the emerging suburbs of Bengaluru.

news.title: Nashik civic body asks shop owners to pay lease at 8% of RR rate
news.para: As per government norms, the NMC had decided to recover lease rate as per 8% of the RR, but shop holders had opposed the new lease rate and moved court on the issue three years ago.

news.title: Hyderabad: HMDA collects Rs 333 crore from second day of land auction in Uppal Bhagat
news.para: Officials were enthused by the good response to the auction as it fetched Rs 474 crore for a single layout at Uppal Bhagat. In the earlier auction from the same layout, the HMDA earned Rs 1,000 crore revenue.
